Description: Diorite-gneiss amulet in the form of the frog-goddess Heket; pierced longitudinally.
Curator's comments: Published in: Andrews, C. 1994. Amulets of Ancient Egypt, p.32; see also p. 63 for frog amulets in general. Regulski, I. (ed.), 2022. Hieroglyphs: unlocking ancient Egypt, p. 207
Bibliographic references: Shaw & Nicholson 1995 / British Museum Dictionary of Ancient Egypt (p124)
Exhibition history: 2022-2023 13 Oct-19 Feb, London, BM, Hieroglyphs: unlocking ancient Egypt
